definition.value: Any O-acylcarnitine in which the carnitine component has L-configuration and the acyl group is a fatty acid.
Any O-acylcarnitine in which the acyl group is a fatty acid and the carnitine component has configuration undefined.
A non-proteinogenic alpha-amino acid in which benzene is ortho-fused onto the C-3-C-4 bond of L-proline.
A diterpene comprising bicyclo[12.1.0]pentadeca-2,6,10-triene having three methyl substituents located at the 3-, 7- and 11-positions as well as gem-dimethyl groups at the 15-position.
